
##
# Contains root .gitignore declarations for the current project instance
# using Common Web Tools.
#

# [customizable] Local environment global variables and other generated files.
/scripts/cwt/local/*
!/scripts/cwt/local/README.md

# [optional] Public web dir or application docroot.
# See $APP_DOCROOT global var help in cwt/env/global.vars.sh.
# There are 2 implementation approaches for using common web tools in a project :
#   1 • Use a single, "monolothic" repo for everything
#   2 • [default] Keep application code in a separate Git repo
# → When using option 1, you may want to comment out the following lines.
# Note: these are common suggestions to adapt to project needs (option 2).
# The app docroot may also be located outside the project root dir.
/docroot
/public
/web
/www

# [optional] Private files, outside of public (web) dir.
/private/*
!/private/README.md
!/private/.htaccess

# [optional] Folders for persisting DB data (volume) + DB dumps of the following
# optional extensions :
# @see cwt/extensions/db
# @see cwt/extensions/mysql
/db
/dumps

# [optional] Docker-compose env file.
# @see cwt/extensions/docker-compose
/.env

# Misc.
docker-runtime
.idea
*.sql
.DS_Store
._*
